Joneal runs $\frac{5280}{50} = 105.6$ laps around the track.  The point where he stops is the same as the point where he started plus $\frac{1}{10}$ of a lap.  Therefore, he stops at point $\frac{1}{10}$ of the way around the circle from point $S.$

[asy]
import graph;
draw(Circle((0,0),20));
draw((-25,0)--(25,0));
draw((0,-25)--(0,25));
dot((20,0));
label("$S$",(20,0),SE);
draw((20,0)--(20,20));
label("$A$",(20,20),NE);
draw((20,0)--(-20,0));
label("$B$",(-20,0),S);
draw((20,0)--(0,-20));
label("$C$",(0,-20),S);
